<subSubSection id="C300650BE84D5843FF52AB64FCCEFC4D" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BA53680E84D5843FF52AB64FCA3FC3D" blockId="11.[144,1105,782,1301]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
Previously recorded material: 
<emphasis id="B96EEA92E84D5843FE59AB65FC07FC85" box="[411,927,783,804]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8B4B71E84D5843FE59AB65FDFEFC85" box="[411,614,783,804]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" refId="ref10603" refString="LONDT, J. G. H. &amp; TSACAS, L. 1987. The genus Congomochtherus Oldroyd, 1970 (Diptera, Asilidae, Asilinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France (N. S.) 23 (1): 29 - 42." type="journal article">Londt &amp; Tsacas (1987)</bibRefCitation>
listed the following type specimens
</emphasis>
: SOUTH AFRICA: 2♂ 2♀ (paratypes), 10 km E Rhodes, bottom Naudesnek Pass [
<emphasis id="B96EEA92E84D5843FD14AB4DFD78FC9D" box="[726,736,807,828]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">c</emphasis>
. 30°47'S 28°00'E, 
<emphasis id="B96EEA92E84D5843FC4DAB4DFC01FC9D" box="[911,921,807,828]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">c</emphasis>
. 1850 m], 3028CC, 9.i.1979, Londt &amp; Stuckenberg, river banks (NMSA); 7♂ (holotype &amp; paratypes) 5♀ (paratypes), Rhodes area [
<emphasis id="B96EEA92E84D5843FF00AB3DFF54FCCD" box="[194,204,855,876]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">c</emphasis>
. 30°47'38&quot;S 27°57'38&quot;E, 
<emphasis id="B96EEA92E84D5843FE77AB3DFE27FCCD" box="[437,447,855,876]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">c</emphasis>
. 1815 m], 3027DD, 9-10.i.1979, Londt &amp; Stuckenberg, banks of river &amp; hill near town (NMSA (holotype 5♂ 3♀ paratypes)*, MNHN, BMNH); 1♂ 1♀ (paratypes), Rhodes village [as above], 9.i.1979, Londt &amp; Stuckenberg, river banks on stones (NMSA).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA53680E84D5843FF52ABCCFCCEFC4D" blockId="11.[144,1105,782,1301]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Newly recorded material: SOUTH AFRICA:1♂, 10 km ENE of Rhodes, 30°45'S 28°01'E, 2080 m, 5.ii.1992, Natal Museum Expedition, causeway near Malpas (NMSA); 4♂ 2♀, Bell River at Rhodes, 30°48'S 27°58'E, 1825 m, 5.ii.1992, Natal Museum Expedition, trees grass &amp; riverine (NMSA).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C300650BE84D5843FF52AB91FD86FAB4" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA53680E84D5843FF52AB91FD86FAB4" blockId="11.[144,1105,782,1301]" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">
Distribution (
<figureCitation id="13212A05E84D5843FEE7AB91FEEEFBB4" box="[293,374,1019,1045]" captionStart="Fig. 17" captionStartId="15.[144,177,1571,1593]" captionTargetBox="[328,920,956,1554]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[329,918,956,1551]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 17. Southern African distribution of Congomochtherus Oldroyd 1979: C. acuminatus Oldroyd, 1974 (circles); C. elferinki Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (squares); C. inachus Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (triangles); C. potamius Londt &amp; Tsacas, 1987 (diamond)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1472912/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
), phenology (
<tableCitation id="C698033BE84D5843FDCFAB91FDC7FBB4" box="[525,607,1019,1045]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[616,691,204,225]" captionTargetBox="[197,1115,280,622]" captionTargetId="graphics@4.[181,1141,268,629]" captionText="TABLE 1 Phenology of Congomochtherus species. Months - starting from July." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF656608E842584CFDAAA8A6FC4BFEA3" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" tableUuid="DF656608E842584CFDAAA8A6FC4BFEA3">Table 1</tableCitation>
) and biology: This South African endemic is confined in its distribution to a small area in the vicinity of the village of Rhodes in the southern Drakensberg Mountains of the Eastern Cape Province. I collected all available specimens on two trips to the area in January and February (
<tableCitation id="C698033BE84D5843FCE7AC31FCEFFBD4" box="[805,887,1115,1141]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[616,691,204,225]" captionTargetBox="[197,1115,280,622]" captionTargetId="graphics@4.[181,1141,268,629]" captionText="TABLE 1 Phenology of Congomochtherus species. Months - starting from July." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF656608E842584CFDAAA8A6FC4BFEA3" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" tableUuid="DF656608E842584CFDAAA8A6FC4BFEA3">Table 1</tableCitation>
). It is probable that the species is active for much of summer in this summer-rainfall region. All specimens were found resting on rocks in the Bell River, which flows along the northern boundary of Rhodes. Efforts to find examples in the vicinity adjacent to the stream were fruitless. The habitat closely resembles that described for 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A4D03E84D5843FD77ACB6FC8AFB57" authorityName="Londt &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1987" box="[693,786,1244,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Congomochtherus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="343" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elferinki">
<emphasis id="B96EEA92E84D5843FD77ACB6FC8AFB57" box="[693,786,1244,1270]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="343">elferinki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There is no biological data apart from that appearing on labels.
</paragraph>
